Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens; mince whites. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Halve, deseed, and slice @long green pepper{1} into 1⁄2-inch strips. Halve, peel, and slice @yellow onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

== Lime Slaw ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the scallion greens, half the lime zest, juice from half the lime, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @guacamole{4%tablespoon} with remaining sour cream. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

== Turkey Patties ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground turkey{10%ounce}, garlic, scallion whites, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, half the @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, remaining lime zest, and 1 TBSP water. Mix gently until thoroughly combined.

> For 4 servings, add 20% more water.

Form turkey mixture into 6 1 1⁄2-inch meatballs (12 meatballs for 4). Set aside on a #plate{}.

> TIP: Coat hands with oil first to prevent sticking.

== Fajita Veggies ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, onion, remaining fajita spice blend, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wash out pan.

== Cook Patties ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add meatballs; gently press down with a #spatula{} to make 1⁄2-inch-thick patties. Cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, cook in batches if necessary.

== To Serve ==

Divide fajita veggies and slaw between plates. Top veggies with turkey patties. Top patties with creamy guacamole and remaining scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.